content:
Lets wax our arms and bleach our face, thread those brows and pluck those strays. Let's curl what's straight and iron what's not, indulge in lasers and whatever else is hot. Let's paint the lips and double-stroke the eyes, see us in the mirror and shriek in delight.

Its why most settle for the trick  beauty doesn't come so easy, pretty could be anybody.

&nbsp;
